    <item>
      <title>THM: The Great Disappearing Act Writeup</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/hagen-kwik-lab/labs/the_great_disappearing_act/</link>
      <pubDate>Tue, 03 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/hagen-kwik-lab/labs/the_great_disappearing_act/</guid>
      <description>&lt;figure&gt;&#xD;&#xA;        &lt;img&#xD;&#xA;          class=&#34;my-0 rounded-md&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          loading=&#34;lazy&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          decoding=&#34;async&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          fetchpriority=&#34;auto&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          alt=&#34;&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          width=&#34;876&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          height=&#34;830&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/hagen-kwik-lab/labs/the_great_disappearing_act/featured_hu_dd34858583fde4ca.png&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          srcset=&#34;http://localhost:1313/hagen-kwik-lab/labs/the_great_disappearing_act/featured_hu_dd34858583fde4ca.png 800w,/hagen-kwik-lab/labs/the_great_disappearing_act/featured_hu_caf61177ccce809c.png 1280w&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          sizes=&#34;(min-width: 768px) 50vw, 65vw&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          data-zoom-src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/hagen-kwik-lab/labs/the_great_disappearing_act/featured.png&#34;&#xD;&#xA;        /&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &#xD;&#xA;  &#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Background Knowledge&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;background-knowledge&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &#xD;&#xA;    &lt;span&#xD;&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#background-knowledge&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This writeup is for &lt;code&gt;The Great Disappearing Act&lt;/code&gt;, a room in TryHackMe (THM) for Advent of Cyber (AoC) 2025 Side Quest&amp;rsquo;s Event. This room focuses on Open-Source Intelligence (OSINT), API Exploitation, and Docker Privilege Escalation.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Open-Source Intelligence (OSINT) involves gathering, analyzing, and making decisions based on data accessible in the public domain.&#xA;More information on OSINT resources can be found through the OSINT Framework website &lt;a href=&#34;https://osintframework.com/&#34;  target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noreferrer&#34;&gt;https://osintframework.com/&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      <media:content xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="http://localhost:1313/hagen-kwik-lab/labs/the_great_disappearing_act/featured.png" />
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>THM: Chains of Love Writeup</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/hagen-kwik-lab/labs/chains_of_love/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 02 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/hagen-kwik-lab/labs/chains_of_love/</guid>
      <description>&lt;figure&gt;&#xD;&#xA;        &lt;img&#xD;&#xA;          class=&#34;my-0 rounded-md&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          loading=&#34;lazy&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          decoding=&#34;async&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          fetchpriority=&#34;auto&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          alt=&#34;&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          width=&#34;1160&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          height=&#34;763&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/hagen-kwik-lab/labs/chains_of_love/featured_hu_ae606df317cf9106.jpg&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          srcset=&#34;http://localhost:1313/hagen-kwik-lab/labs/chains_of_love/featured_hu_ae606df317cf9106.jpg 800w,/hagen-kwik-lab/labs/chains_of_love/featured_hu_36a806a9c1af7948.jpg 1280w&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          sizes=&#34;(min-width: 768px) 50vw, 65vw&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          data-zoom-src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/hagen-kwik-lab/labs/chains_of_love/featured.jpg&#34;&#xD;&#xA;        /&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &#xD;&#xA;  &#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Background Knowledge&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;background-knowledge&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &#xD;&#xA;    &lt;span&#xD;&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#background-knowledge&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This writeup is for &lt;code&gt;Chains of Love&lt;/code&gt;, a room in TryHackMe (THM) for Valentine&amp;rsquo;s 2026 Event. This room focuses on Server-Side Request Forgery (SSRF), JWT exploitation, and security misconfigurations leading to information disclosure via exposed Git repositories.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;h3 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;JSON Web Token (JWT)&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;json-web-token-jwt&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &#xD;&#xA;    &lt;span&#xD;&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#json-web-token-jwt&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h3&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;A JWT (JSON Web Token) is a cryptographic signature specifically generated for each website visitor. It helps the website remember who you are and is typically stored in the cookie for authentication, authorization and session management. A standard JWT token consist of 3 parts. They are header, Payload and Signature.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      <media:content xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="http://localhost:1313/hagen-kwik-lab/labs/chains_of_love/featured.jpg" />
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>THM: LoveLetterLock Writeup</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/hagen-kwik-lab/labs/loveletterlock/</link>
      <pubDate>Sun, 01 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/hagen-kwik-lab/labs/loveletterlock/</guid>
      <description>&lt;figure&gt;&#xD;&#xA;        &lt;img&#xD;&#xA;          class=&#34;my-0 rounded-md&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          loading=&#34;lazy&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          decoding=&#34;async&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          fetchpriority=&#34;auto&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          alt=&#34;&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          width=&#34;1155&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          height=&#34;716&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/hagen-kwik-lab/labs/loveletterlock/featured_hu_7856ea7464323348.jpg&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          srcset=&#34;http://localhost:1313/hagen-kwik-lab/labs/loveletterlock/featured_hu_7856ea7464323348.jpg 800w,/hagen-kwik-lab/labs/loveletterlock/featured_hu_b6c7e5721a8c5a53.jpg 1280w&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          sizes=&#34;(min-width: 768px) 50vw, 65vw&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          data-zoom-src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/hagen-kwik-lab/labs/loveletterlock/featured.jpg&#34;&#xD;&#xA;        /&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &#xD;&#xA;  &#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Background Knowledge&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;background-knowledge&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &#xD;&#xA;    &lt;span&#xD;&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#background-knowledge&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This writeup is for &lt;code&gt;LoveLetterLock&lt;/code&gt;, a room in TryHackMe (THM) for Valentine&amp;rsquo;s 2026 Event. This room focuses on Insecure Direct Object References (IDOR) Vulnerability.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Insecure Direct Object References (IDOR) occurs when an attacker is able to access unauthorized data by manipulating its identifiers. This usually happens due to weak access control implementations, where systems fails to verify if a user actually has the proper authorization towards that specific data.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      <media:content xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="http://localhost:1313/hagen-kwik-lab/labs/loveletterlock/featured.jpg" />
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>THM: CupidBot Writeup</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/hagen-kwik-lab/labs/cupidbot/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 28 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/hagen-kwik-lab/labs/cupidbot/</guid>
      <description>&lt;figure&gt;&#xD;&#xA;        &lt;img&#xD;&#xA;          class=&#34;my-0 rounded-md&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          loading=&#34;lazy&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          decoding=&#34;async&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          fetchpriority=&#34;auto&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          alt=&#34;&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          width=&#34;1292&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          height=&#34;683&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/hagen-kwik-lab/labs/cupidbot/featured_hu_8c89d2a140e956e0.jpg&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          srcset=&#34;http://localhost:1313/hagen-kwik-lab/labs/cupidbot/featured_hu_8c89d2a140e956e0.jpg 800w,/hagen-kwik-lab/labs/cupidbot/featured_hu_9967e1e1d58a17f8.jpg 1280w&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          sizes=&#34;(min-width: 768px) 50vw, 65vw&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          data-zoom-src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/hagen-kwik-lab/labs/cupidbot/featured.jpg&#34;&#xD;&#xA;        /&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &#xD;&#xA;  &#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Background Knowledge&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;background-knowledge&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &#xD;&#xA;    &lt;span&#xD;&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#background-knowledge&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This writeup is for &lt;code&gt;CupidBot&lt;/code&gt;, a room in TryHackMe (THM) for Valentine&amp;rsquo;s 2026 Event. This room focuses on Prompt Injection.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Prompt Injection is a vulnerabitlity where an attacker crafts malicious input to feed into the Large Language Model (LLM). The goal is to bypass its model&amp;rsquo;s filters, resulting in an output/action that should otherwise be restricted.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      <media:content xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="http://localhost:1313/hagen-kwik-lab/labs/cupidbot/featured.jpg" />
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>THM: Cupids Matchmaker Writeup</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/hagen-kwik-lab/labs/cupids_matchmaker/</link>
      <pubDate>Fri, 27 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/hagen-kwik-lab/labs/cupids_matchmaker/</guid>
      <description>&lt;figure&gt;&#xD;&#xA;        &lt;img&#xD;&#xA;          class=&#34;my-0 rounded-md&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          loading=&#34;lazy&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          decoding=&#34;async&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          fetchpriority=&#34;auto&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          alt=&#34;&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          width=&#34;1153&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          height=&#34;697&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/hagen-kwik-lab/labs/cupids_matchmaker/featured_hu_4d9cd7e5d68bfac.jpg&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          srcset=&#34;http://localhost:1313/hagen-kwik-lab/labs/cupids_matchmaker/featured_hu_4d9cd7e5d68bfac.jpg 800w,/hagen-kwik-lab/labs/cupids_matchmaker/featured_hu_876de87102d181a3.jpg 1280w&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          sizes=&#34;(min-width: 768px) 50vw, 65vw&#34;&#xD;&#xA;          data-zoom-src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/hagen-kwik-lab/labs/cupids_matchmaker/featured.jpg&#34;&#xD;&#xA;        /&gt;&#xD;&#xA;  &#xD;&#xA;  &#xD;&#xA;  &lt;/figure&gt;&#xA;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Background Knowledge&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;background-knowledge&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &#xD;&#xA;    &lt;span&#xD;&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xD;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#background-knowledge&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xD;&#xA;    &#xD;&#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xD;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;This writeup is for &lt;code&gt;Cupids Matchmaker&lt;/code&gt;, a room in TryHackMe (THM) for Valentine&amp;rsquo;s 2026 Event. This room focuses on XSS Vulnerability.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Cross-Site Scripting (XSS) is a condition when a web application accepts untrusted data from a user and sends it to a web browser without proper sanitazion. This allows an attacker to inject and execute malicious scripts (usually JavaScript) within the victim&amp;rsquo;s website. There are 3 main types of XXS. They are Stored, Reflected, and Blind XSS.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      <media:content xmlns:media="http://search.yahoo.com/mrss/" url="http://localhost:1313/hagen-kwik-lab/labs/cupids_matchmaker/featured.jpg" />
    </item>
    
